<h1>Sneak Attack</h1>
<p>Sneak Attack, an ability associated with the rogue core class, is used across a myriad of other classes and prestige classes in modified form. Bonus damage typically stacks, unless the ability is renamed.</p>
<h2>Classes</h2>
<h2>- Rogue</h2>
<h2>Prestige Classes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Rogue</li>
<li>Assassin</li>
<li>Shadowdancer</li>
<li>Blackguard</li>
<li>Spellthief</li>
</ul>
<p>Classless limits: Experience rank? (+1 at 1st level and increases by +1 every 4 levels thereafter)</p>
<p>Bonuses do stack.</p>
<h2>Skirmish (Scout)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Modified conditions (movement instead of sneakiness)</li>
<li>Alternate between gaining +1d6 extra damage and +1AC every two levels.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Sudden Strike (Ninja)</h2>
